The Director is hereby authorized to resolve by settlement any notice of violation or lawsuit initiated by the Director. In deciding to settle a dispute over an alleged violation, the County shall consider:


The probability of success in proving the violation;



The nature and seriousness of the violation;



The Registrant's past history concerning similar violations;



Mitigating factors; and



The Registrant's success in resolving the dispute with affected customers.
